---
import Base from "../../layouts/Base.astro";
---

<Base
  title="Workplace Support · Ennea Evolution"
  description="Some things at work need more than another meeting. Confidential, neutral support for the people situations a manager shouldn't have to carry alone."
>
  <div style="--accent:#2BA1A3;">
    <!-- PANEL 1 · white · hero -->
    <section class="panel">
      <div class="container narrow">
        <p class="eyebrow">Professional Work</p>
        <h1>Workplace Support</h1>
        <h3 style="margin-bottom:1.25rem;">Some things at work need more than another meeting.</h3>
        <p class="lead">Confidential, neutral support for the people situations a manager shouldn't have to carry alone.</p>
        <p>Two good people who can't seem to work together. Someone who's gone quiet, or whose work has started to slip, and no one's sure why. A tension everyone can feel and nobody wants to name. Situations like these don't fit inside a meeting, and they don't belong to one manager to solve alone.</p>
        <p>That doesn't mean anything is wrong with your team. Every workplace has these. Some things are simply bigger than a status update, or they have been sitting too long, or they need someone the people involved can be completely honest with.</p>
        <a href="/get-started" class="btn" style="margin-top:0.75rem;">Let's Talk</a>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- PANEL 2 · tint #CCD8DE · quote band -->
    <section class="panel-tight tint-band" style="--tint:#CCD8DE;">
      <div class="container">
        <blockquote class="pullquote testimonial" style="margin-block:1rem;">
          "It gave us a way to talk about tension without making it personal."
          <cite>Executive Team Member (draft quote, confirm before launch)</cite>
        </blockquote>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- PANEL 3 · white -->
    <section class="panel">
      <div class="container narrow">
        <h3>What this is</h3>
        <p>The confidential, human side of the work, for the people situations a meeting or a manager can't resolve on their own. Sometimes that is support for one person. Sometimes it is two people who need help hearing each other. Sometimes it is a whole situation that has gone quiet without going away.</p>

        <h3 style="margin-top:2.5rem;">What it can look like</h3>
        <ul class="marklist">
          <li><strong>A confidential ear.</strong> Someone from outside the company an employee can actually talk to, when they are carrying something, or stuck on something, and don't know where to take it.</li>
          <li><strong>Mediation.</strong> When two people can't figure each other out, a neutral third person who helps them hear each other again, so they can get back to working together.</li>
          <li><strong>The conversation that keeps not happening.</strong> A facilitated version of the hard conversation that has been avoided, or that keeps going south when the same people attempt it alone.</li>
          <li><strong>Thinking room for leaders.</strong> A place for a manager or a leader to work through a stuck people-situation with someone who isn't in the middle of it.</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- PANEL 4 · white · 50/50 split: photo left, copy right -->
    <section class="panel" style="padding-top:0;">
      <div class="container split">
        <div class="photo-block" style="--block:#CCD8DE;">
          <div class="photo-slot" style="--tint:#ffffff;">
            <span>Photo: two chairs by a window, or two people talking in soft light. Quiet, dignified, hopeful</span>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div>
          <h3>Why it works from the outside</h3>
          <p>Even the best manager is in the middle of it. Even the best HR team sits inside the company. Some situations simply need a neutral outsider, someone with no stake and no reporting line, that people can be honest with in a way they can't always be internally.</p>
          <p>This is the work I already do, every week. Half of my time is spent in confidential one-on-one conversations, helping people work through the things they can't say anywhere else. Bringing that into a workplace isn't a stretch for me. It's the same craft in a different room. And because I come from outside your company, people tend to tell me the thing they've been holding back.</p>
          <blockquote class="pullquote" style="margin-block:1.5rem 0;">That's usually the thing that moves the whole situation.</blockquote>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- PANEL 5 · white -->
    <section class="panel" style="padding-top:0;">
      <div class="container narrow">
        <h3>How it works</h3>
        <p>Some companies bring this in for a specific situation. Others fold it into a partnership: a regular check-in with each person on a smaller team, a standing session with leaders on a larger one. It is custom by company, ad hoc or ongoing, as much or as little as a situation actually needs.</p>

        <h3 style="margin-top:2.5rem;">What's possible</h3>
        <p>The person everyone quietly learned to work around is back in the flow of the team. Two people who couldn't work together can. Someone who was carrying something heavy has somewhere to turn.</p>
        <p>And the situations that used to just sit there start finding their way through.</p>
      </div>
    </section>

    <hr class="hairline-gold" />

    <!-- PANEL 6 · white · centered close -->
    <section class="panel center">
      <div class="container narrow">
        <h3>Let's talk it through</h3>
        <p>Tell me what's going on. I'll tell you whether I can help, and what it would look like.</p>
        <a href="/get-started" class="btn" style="margin-top:0.5rem;">Let's Talk</a>
      </div>
    </section>
  </div>
</Base>
